reviews.text: I've come to Taka so many times and it never disappointed me. Make sure you make a reservation on weekends! Great service unless it's very busy, but reasonable. Outstanding owner, awesome atmosphere and phenomenal food! Also Take Away, you can call and pre-order. One of the best places in town for sure.

Went here for Valentine's Day with my husband for the first time after dying to try this place. LOVED it! The atmosphere was so trendy and inviting. The decor is gorgeous. Our server helped me with sushi choices and he was very knowledgeable. We also got teriyaki chicken meatballs and they were awesome! They are a large portion for the value. For dinner, I got the Salmon topped with Japanese BBQ. It was perfectly cooked. The sauce was delicious and the sides were great. It was not hard to finish the whole thing. will definitely be back!
Don't let the smaller menu size fool you- they are experts in cooking everything on it. Waiting staff is great as well. Will definitely be back.

Very lively place on a Saturday evening. Without reservations the wait was 1-1/2 hours around 8:00 PM, but the staff were so accommodating they found a spot at the bar for me. In spite of the crowds, the service was excellent. Thanks Mike! The Soba soup was grand, but the Calamari has too much batter for my taste. All in all a great experience.

Fantastic egg crepe with shrimp tempura. Pair it with hot sake to enjoy it. 

Definitely great ambience with a boisterous crowd if you like it.

I've been here three times. Looks clean and pretty good service, no problems finding a parking spot. The food is good and I would give more stars if they would get my order right. I ordered three orders of veggie rice without egg. Every time at least one of the orders has had egg and even once got egg and chicken. After the second time my SO complained that his rice was crunchy.

Did this place get new owners?  Cash only with an atm in the entryway. (3$ for those who don't carry cash).  We ordered lunch here and the vegetable curry was kind of cold. The rest if the food was cool too. A little heavy on the red pepper so watch the spice level. The food just wasn't the same. Haven't been here in about a year but, it wasn't the same.  Service was ok. Lunch for 2 with soup and an app was 36.00.
Best place to get Thai food..... If you love spicy food come here.... They also have other selection of you don't like spicy food
Food very ordinary.  I love Thai food but this one is near the bottom.  I went with a friend.  Both of our meals were slightly hotter than room temperature.  Pretty boring.  Not recommended.
must be under new ownership. seems the quality of food has changed as well as they are now cash only? not a fan
Friendly staff, nice food. We had a banquet for 7 people with a pile of beers. Loads of well prepared, tasty food and reasonably priced as well.
Really nice surroundings lovely friendly staff and great food.  Brilliant value for money.  Well worth a visit.
Fantastic food and friendly service. Only place that has good aromatic crispy duck. They make some great food.
Would give zero stars if possible. Food was terrible, and the service was even worse! Avoid like the plague.
Remember that You have to pay extra money for rice. Beef was... lets say "good" and the service really nice.

We walked into this warm and friendly coffeehouse to be greeted by a delicious range of cakes (as shown in the photo) and the smell of home cooking. The food is superb and reasonably priced. The staff are friendly, efficient and serve you quickly. This is a popular place with locals and the long opening hours help to spread out the demand. We returned here every day for breakfast which was far superior to the hotel we were staying in. Well worth a visit for breakfast lunch or tea. Recommend the chocolate penut butter stack cake, delicious.😋
Great menu choices. Really kind and helpful staff. Cute place. Excellent food. Glad we found this one.
Cosy, small pleasant atmosphere. Good prices and great service
Great little place - visited with my daughter and the staff were really nice. We had a light snacks but my daughter said it was the best Cheese toastie she's ever had! Will visit again
Lamb stew was amazing.  Staff very helpful xxxx glad a table was reserved for us as we cycled 50 miles in headwinds all the way and it was worth it!
